pgTitle: List of former territorial authorities in New Zealand

rows.text: Amalgamated with Waitomo to form Otorohanga County
Amalgamated with Takaka County to form Golden Bay County.
Amalgamated with Wallace County in 1981, at which time it was "the only one of 105 counties where the Counties Act (1956) is not wholly in force"
Amalgamated with Levels County to form Strathallan County
Amalgamated with Geraldine County to form Strathallan County
Formed from the Makara Riding of Hutt County. Remnant amalgamated with Hutt County when Porirua Borough established.
Amalgamated with Rangiora borough to form Rangiora District.
Amalgamated with Marlborough County prior to 1913.
Amalgamated with Collingwood County to form Golden Bay County.
Separated from Cook County 10 December 1918. Amalgamated with Cook County 1 April 1964.
Became part of Central Otago District
Amalgamated with Ashley County to form Hurunui County.
Created in 1876 but first Council did not meet until 1877
